\sub מַשְׁבֵּר ,מִשְׁבָּר ,שָׁבוּר ,שֶׁבֶר ,שִׁבָּרוֹן ,שְׁבָרִים
\intro 1.  The verb |hשׁבר|h* ‘to buy (grain)’ generally refers to a commercial transaction that involves the purchase of grain and other food items from another human for a price. 2. In the Hiphil,  the verb |hשׁבר|h* ‘to buy (grain)’ refers to a commercial transaction that involves the sale of grain to another human for a price. 3. The verb |hשׁבר|h* is, however, more frequently used to refer to a variety of other meanings such as "to shatter; to break, etc."
\comp Meanings 1-2 are the only meanings relevant for the Commercial Transaction frame. Meanings 3-10 are other meanings from a variety of domains that have not been thoroughly analyzed.Meaning 1. Commercial transaction as seen from the perspective of the buyer Meaning 2. Commercial transaction as seen from the perspective of the seller.Meanings 3-4. Refer to the breaking of inanimate objects or parts of animate objects. Meaning 4 is a more intensified form of the breaking action in which the inanimate object is left in small pieces. Meaning 5. Refers to the injuring of an animate being. The nature of the injury can be either fatal or non-fatal. Meaning 6. Extension of meaning 3 that refers to destruction or defeat of individuals or socio-political entities. Meaning 7. Extension of meaning 3 that refers to the fact that certain states or abstract entities cease to exist. Meaning 8. Extension of meaning 3 that refers to the emotional effect of damage to one's spiritual or emotional sense of well-being.  Meaning 9. Extension of meaning 3 that refers to God's role in childbirth.Meaning 10. A seemingly unrelated meaning that refers to setting a boundary in place.
\dfnotes Unlike other terms in the Economic Domain, |hשׁבר|h*  'to buy (grain)' seems to be limited to the sale/purchase of grain and food.
\level2 1
\meaning To buy (grain); To acquire ownership of grain and other food items from another human in exchange for money or other items considered to be equal in value
