\keyverse NIV - “But I tell you, in this you are not |bright|b*, for God is greater than man
\eval Most translations render by 'you are not right' or conversely, 'you are wrong'. Either of these may be followed. REB, 'you are not in the right' seems to introduce a legal nuance that is not present in the context and should not be followed.
\ref 2!;!%#" 2!A!,""|ng|n* 7!K!)."|nh|n*
\paradigc Causative
\pgloss to declare or acknowledge that someone is right
