\intro ·	The term always has connotations of conformity to a norm·	This is particularly clear in those cases where the term is used to describe weights and measures that match the standard.·	In various other contexts, that norm is the covenant, wisdom principles or, more rarely, societal norms·	Most often, it describes general human behaviour according to a norm·	A person’s status in the eyes of a community may be distinguished from that person’s behaviour, but they are never separated. People have righteous status because their behaviour is righteous.·	It is used of human rulers and judges when they fulfil their duty according to the appropriate norm·	It is used of God when he acts in accordance with the covenant, either in giving well-being to faithful Israel or punishing unfaithful Israel.·	It is used of sacrifices that are in accordance with the norm of the law
