\intro ·	The term always has connotations of conformity to a norm·	In various contexts, that norm is the covenant, wisdom principles or, more rarely, societal norms·	Most often, it describes general human behaviour according to a norm·	A person’s status in the eyes of a community may be distinguished from that person’s behaviour, but they are never separated. People have righteous status because their behaviour is righteous.·	In a few cases the term is used for the well-being that was believed to result from righteous behaviour·	It is used of human rulers and judges when they fulfil their duty according to the appropriate norm·	It is used of God when he acts in accordance with the covenant, either in giving well-being to faithful Israel or punishing unfaithful Israel.·	In two case it is used for a legal right or claim, an extension of the use for rulers and judges when they fulfil their duty
