\intro 1. The term |hשָׂכִיר|h* is used most frequently to refer to a person that has been given money or other valuable items in order to perform a particular service or work.  In other words, this adjective is used as a noun, referring to a temporary attribute. 2. The hired person may be either a general worker or a soldier.3. The term may also be used to refer to animals whose owners are given money for the use of their services. 4. The term is used with an extended meaning ('hired razor') for someone that God uses to perform a task.
\comp Meaning 1. Refers to the recipient of money who is also the agent performing an activityMeaning 2. Refers to the agent performing an activity whose owner has been given moneyMeaning 3. Refers to an entity used by God to perform an activity
