\intro 1. The meanings of this word are all related to a central meaning, ‘to advise, to counsel’ (except Meaning 6, 'wood').2. The relative social status of the people giving and receiving advice helps distinguish the meanings.3. Most commonly it is used where wise people advise other people who are higher in status (Meaning 1).4. Sometimes it denotes the process of social equals conferring together (Meaning 2).5. Sometimes it is used to describe the outcome of deliberation with others or with oneself, i.e. when someone plans what he wants to do in the future (Meaning 3).6. Sometimes it is used when there is only one person involved, who can take counsel with hemself and is able to manage something wisely (Meaning 4).7. It can also denote the character dispostion that is needed for wise management (Meaning 5).
