\not (d) For the anomalous form |hעֲצָתַיִךְ|h* in Isa 47:13, see Gesenius / Kautzsch, |iHebrew Grammar|i*, par. 91l. It is a singular form with a (mistaken?) plural suffix. But since the meaning is clearly that the people addressed |ioften|i* obtained advice from soothsayers, it is as well to translate as if it were a regular plural.In this context, |hעֵצָה|h* means 'advice obtained by an oracle or magic'. The verb |hיעץ|h* is also used once in this sense (Num 24:14). See the entry |hיעץ|h* for a discussion of it.
